Welcome to Mora and the **World MTB Orienteering Championships 2026**!

The Swedish Orienteering Federation and IFK Mora Orienteering Club are thrilled to invite athletes, spectators, and families to a week of world-class mountain bike orienteering in the heart of Dalarna. This event also serves as **Round 2 of the 2026 CX80 World Cup**.

{% EventBlogList title="Latest Updates" category="wmtboc26" excludeSlug="wmtboc26" compact=true /%}

## Experience Mora

Mora is more than just a host city; it's a legendary sports destination. Deeply rooted in outdoor tradition, Mora is the finish line for the historic [Vasaloppet](https://vasaloppet.se/en/), the world's oldest and biggest cross-country ski race, and [Cykelvasan](https://www.vasaloppet.se/en/summer/), a massive MTB event.

The event is organized by [IFK Mora Orienteering Club](https://www.svenskalag.se/ifkmora-ok), a club with extensive experience in hosting major international events in orienteering, MTBO, and Ski-O. Together with the local community, we are preparing an unforgettable championship.

## The Terrain

Forget what you know about Falun! The terrain for WMTBOC 2026 offers a completely different experience. We are heading to the pine forests and detailed contours similar to **Mora By (Säterbygden)**, where the relay and Middle distance were held during the 2022 World Cup.

_Note: Mora By (Säterbygden) is a different village ~100km south of Mora, but the terrain characteristics are the inspiration._

The terrain features fast riding, intricate trail networks, and good visibility — pure MTBO enjoyment!

