## Open Public Races

It's not just for the national teams! We are organizing **Open Public Races** in conjunction with the World Championships. These races are part of the **Swedish Veteran Cup**, so come and race on the same high-quality maps and courses.

Everyone is welcome—bring your bike and join the party!

## Plan Your Trip

**Getting Here:**
Mora is easily accessible. The most common route is flying to **Stockholm Arlanda Airport (ARN)** and taking a direct train or rental car to Mora (approx. 3.5 - 4 hours).

**Accommodation:**
The **Event Center (EC)** is located at [Moraparken](https://en.firstcamp.se/destinations/moraparken-dalarna), a beautiful holiday resort by the river. It offers hotel rooms, cabins, and camping—everything you need in one place.

## Status & Preparations

Preparations are in full swing!

- **Maps:** The competition maps have been drawn during the summer of 2025 by **Viktor Larsson**. Viktor is not only an experienced mapper but also a high-level MTBO athlete, former Swedish Long Distance Champion, ensuring the maps are perfectly optimized for the sport.
- **Controlling:** Overseeing the map and technical quality is **Steven Hale**, a legend in British orienteering and experienced map controller. Steven has a distinguished career as a competitor (WOC Silver Medalist) and has surveyed maps for numerous major MTBO events, guaranteeing world-class standards.
- **Courses:** The course setting team is led by Henrik Johnsson, Gustav Johnsson, Erik Rost, and Andrey Lamov. This team comprises elite SkiO and MTBO athletes who know exactly what it takes to create challenging and fair championship courses.
- **Webcam:** Check out the terrain right now via the [Hemus Ski Stadium webcam](https://kamera.mora.se/cam.php?cam=2). Watch the snow production in winter, the Vasaloppet finish in March, and the snow melting in spring!

**Latest Updates:**

- **2025-02-15**: [Bulletin 1 published](https://eventor.orienteering.org/Events/Show/8277) - containing initial details.

